sql:
SELECT DISTINCT u.user_name
FROM users u
INNER JOIN tasks t ON u.user_id = t.assigned_to;

external_knowledge:
- "blossoming tasks" refers to tasks that have progressed significantly, which in this case, are at least commented on more than five times;
- "garden of 'Project X'" is a metaphor for 'Project X';
- "tended to by more than five gardeners" means the tasks have more than five comments;
- "seedling caretakers" refers to the creators of the tasks;
- "mere garden assistants" refers to users with the 'employee' role.

- 'significant importance' refers to tasks with priority levels 'High' or 'Medium';
- 'pending status' indicates tasks that are not yet completed;
- 'exceed a couple in number' means more than 2 projects;
- 'details of the tasks' include the task titles, priority levels, and statuses.

- "gardeners" represent the users;
- "watered their plants" symbolizes the act of completing tasks;
- "barely watered their plants" implies spending very little time on tasks;
- "from the most attentive to the least" is understood as sorting by average time spent per task from highest to lowest.
